    dc:description "A chemical graph is a structural descriptor in which the connectivity and constitution of the chemical entity are described in terms of a mathematical graph, usually with atoms as vertices and bonds as edges, but other variants exist." ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/pink/cheminf#> ;
